As a seasoned Buyer's Broker with excellent negotiating, communication, and project management skills, I am also an expert in Relocation and Short-Sales. 
No matter what your real estate needs are, expect a tireless effort designed to ensure that you are completely satisfied and engaged. I will provide the real estate experience, service, and dedication that you need to get the results you deserve. Making me your real estate expert - for sure!

agents.description:
Los Angeles Westside native with over a billion dollars sold in residential real estate, David Solomon consistently ranks in the Wall Street Journals annual list of top 250 agents in the United States. In 2019, his sales topped 170,000,000 ranking him one of the top producing agents at his firm, Douglas Elliman. Having recently joined Douglas Elliman, coming from a position as partner at The Agency, David at the time had set out to join an industry-disrupting brokerage that would redefine the business of real estate. Prior to The Agencys inception in 2011, David had spent nearly a decade at Prudential California Realty, which later became Berkshire Hathaway, and was often ranked in the top 10 in the entire company.
 
As an early adopter of technology, web, video, social media, and a keen eye for real estate marketing, David exponentially grew his business year-over-year, even when the market was seemingly collapsing in the 2008 downturn. David prides his business in being able to deliver world-class marketing with aggressive, but delicate sales and negotiation skills, white-glove service, and handling every transaction and client with the utmost discretion.  A natural born sales person with a true passion for people, his clients often become friends for life. Davids clients are comprised of a wide variety of fields from top tech entrepreneurs, celebrities, athletes, entertainment execs, business moguls, foreign investors, and more.
 
Having grown up in the business and now spending nearly 15 years in it himself, David has seen the ups and downs of different markets. Beyond just selling real estate for clients, David has bought, designed, built, and sold numerous properties, and continues to own and rent out a handful of prime coastal properties. Davids biggest passions aside from family, include surfing, traveling, photography, art, design, and architecture. When David is not working he can often be found spending time with his family, and his favorite activity is snowboarding with his six-year-old son Greyson when time permits.

A native Angeleno, Austin Lemon is inherently predisposed to seeing real estate as a lifestyle. Immersed in the particularly prestigious properties of Santa Monica and the greater Westside, he brings passion, personality and an unparalleled grasp of the citys real estate to The Agency.

Born and raised in Santa Monica, Austins love of the city is second to none. A Westsider through and through, his expert knowledge of L.A.s premier neighborhoods, particularly those of Santa Monicas North of Montana neighborhood and its prized Palisades Tract, where he grew up; as well as Pacific Palisades, from Rustic Canyon to the Alphabet Streets and The Highlands; and Brentwood, from Mandeville and Kenter Canyons to Brentwood Park and beyond, makes him an asset to his clients. Having watched these neighborhoods grow and evolve over the course of his lifetime, he is deeply in tune with the nuances of each market and equipped to help buyers and sellers make the best possible decisions. With a background in real estate management and alternative dispute resolution, Austins understanding of the complexities of compromise and negotiation has proven invaluable in real estate. Sensitive, intuitive and communicative, he serves as a patient and knowledgeable guide through every step of a transaction.

When Austins not representing his clients in real estate, you can find him walking his Pomeranian, Romeo, in Santa Monicas Palisades Park, hiking the Temescal Canyon trails, lunching in Downtown Santa Monica or the Palisades and spending time with his family. An avid history buff, he loves to pore over the Santa Monica Public Librarys image archive and scout for local historical locations and landmarks. Though theres nowhere hed rather call home than L.A.s Westside, his travels have taken him as far as Bali, Indonesia and Zanzibar, Tanzania. He is a member of the North of Montana Association in Santa Monica
